A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL OFFENSES -- WEAPONS
Introduced By: Senators McKenney, DiPalma, Sosnowski, LaMountain, and Bissaillon
Date Introduced: February 13, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 11-47 of the General Laws entitled "Weapons" is hereby amended
2 by adding thereto the following section:
3 11-47-65. Multiple firearm purchases prohibited.
4 (a) Except as provided pursuant to subsection (b) of this section, no person shall purchase
5 or take possession of more than one firearm in any thirty (30) day period. For purposes of this
6 section, "firearm" means any "pistol", "rifle" or "shotgun" as defined in § 11-47-2.
7 (b) The provisions of subsection (a) of this section shall not apply to federally licensed
8 firearm dealers; governmental entities; any issuance of weapons by a governmental entity to
9 officers, agents or personnel of the governmental entity; law enforcement officers exempt pursuant
10 to the provisions of §§ 11-47-9 and 11-47-9.1; licensed private security companies for use by
11 registered armed security guards; any transfer pursuant to a court order; an estate representative or
12 heir in accordance with an authorization issued or ordered by a probate court; a temporary rental
13 or use of a firearm at a licensed shooting range or club; a participant in a training, firearm safety or
14 shooting course of instruction during the period of instruction; or a transfer of a weapon defined as
15 a curio or relic pursuant to 27 C.F.R. § 478.11 to a licensed curio or relic collector.
16 (c) Any person violating the provisions of subsection (a) of this section upon conviction
17 for a first offense shall be guilty of a misdemeanor and may be sentenced to a term of imprisonment
18 of not more than one year or fined five hundred dollars ($500), or both. Any person convicted of a
19 second or subsequent offense shall be guilty of a felony offense and may be sentenced to a period

1 of confinement not to exceed three (3) years or fined three thousand dollars ($3,000), or both.
2 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
